17 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
18 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1210.900 of Title 70, unless
19 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
20 A. Sections 1 through 7 of this act shall be known and may be
21 cited as the “Oklahoma Math Achievement and Proficiency Act”.
22 B. The Legislature finds that it is essential for children
23 enrolled in the public schools in this state to develop strong
24 mathematical proficiency early and consistently. The Legislature
